<section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="eyebrow">THE METHOD</div>
        <h1>Earn first. Everything else follows.</h1>
        <p class="hero__subhead">Community marketing goes wrong in predictable ways — usually because someone tried to shortcut trust. Our whole method is built to not do that.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="eyebrow">THE PRINCIPLES</div>
        <ol class="tenets">
            <li>
                <div>
                    <h3>Earn first, ask later.</h3>
                    <p>Standing before selling. We build a genuine presence in a community — answering questions, adding context, being useful — before a client's name ever comes up. By the time it does, we've earned the right to say it.</p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <div>
                    <h3>No astroturf, ever.</h3>
                    <p>No fake accounts. No bought upvotes. No sock puppets seeding "organic" praise. No drive-by pitches from burner profiles. Beyond being wrong, it backfires: communities are better at spotting shills than any spam filter, and they remember. One discovered fake costs more trust than a hundred honest comments earn.</p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <div>
                    <h3>Respect the room.</h3>
                    <p>Norms first, always. Every community has its own rules — written and unwritten — about self-promotion, tone, and what counts as contributing. We learn them before we say a word.</p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <div>
                    <h3>Say true things.</h3>
                    <p>We'd rather be useful and honest than polished and empty. If a product isn't the right fit for someone in a thread, we say so. That's exactly why the recommendation counts when it is.</p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <div>
                    <h3>Measure what's real.</h3>
                    <p>Share of voice, qualified traffic, sentiment, branded search lift, and the conversations we can point to. We'll tell you what we can attribute, what we can't, and report both without spin.</p>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="eyebrow">HOW AN ENGAGEMENT RUNS</div>
        <h2>Four phases. No funnel diagram.</h2>
        <div class="phases">
            <div class="phase">
                <h3>Listen &amp; map</h3>
                <p>Where your people actually gather, what they care about, and what each room rewards. The map before the moves.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="phase">
                <h3>Earn standing</h3>
                <p>Show up, contribute, become known. The slow part — and the part everyone else skips.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="phase">
                <h3>Scale presence</h3>
                <p>More rooms, more formats, more surface area — without ever outrunning the trust we've built.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="phase">
                <h3>Report &amp; compound</h3>
                <p>What moved, what we learned, what compounds next. Receipts, not vibes.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

